Consider an unsteady three-dimensional boundary layer flow of an electrically conducting Eyring-Powell fluid past a convectively heated stretching sheet in the presence of nanoparticles. The Cartesian coordinates (x, y, z) are chosen with the origin O and the sheet coincides with the plane at z = 0 and flow occupies the region z > 0 as shown in Fig. 1. By keeping the origin fixed, the sheet is stretched in two laterals x- and ydirections with the velocities respectively in the form;
uwðx; tÞ ¼ ax 1 at and vwðy; tÞ ¼ by 1 at ð2:1Þ
where a and b are positive constants.
